title: For Sale:  THE BIGGEST REASON 22 LR IS SO HARD TO GET
postcontent:
I have seen many people post many different blogs regarding the availability, or more appropriately the lack of availability of 22 LR. 
Like most people, I have blamed the resellers. But, the sad truth is that they are only a symptom of the actual problem.
22 LR production is in high gear, but where is it all going?  The retailers we used to buy from are not putting it on the shelf. Not because they are not receiving shipments, but because they can sell it for 4-5 times as much online. 
Even our favorite outdoor stores have figured out that if they sell it online, that they can advertise it at the same price as it would sell for off the shelf, but charge ammo surcharges or shipping and handling far in excess of the actual shipping costs.

Think about this for a minute. Why would you put a box on the shelf for $25.00 if you can sell it online for $99.99 and never have to listen to a customer complain about the price?

WHAT'S THE SOLUTION?  DO NOT BUY ANY AMMO ONLINE, "EVER" until the availability on the shelf is what it should be! This is the only thing that will get us back to where we should be. Never, never buy ammo online! 
If we all follow this simple rule the ammo will come back to the shelves at fair prices and even the online retailers will have to sell for reasonable and fair prices again!

Copy and paste this everywhere you can. This will work!
